def gridConsolidate(pgrid,sLogFile,verbose=True):
    """read gridsearch log file, 
    update local log, 
    identify prerun gridpoints
    trim gridpoints
    """
    
    gridRuns = [] # reset local log
    
    # read the tuning log (if any)
    file = open(sLogFile,'rb')
    read = True
    while read:
        try:
            gridRuns.append(pickle.load(file))
        except:
            read = False
    file.close()
    
    # list previously searched grids
    if len(gridRuns)>0:
        grids = [i[:-3] for i in gridRuns]
    else:
        grids = []
    
    # delete pre-evaluated gridpoints (if any)
    for gp in grids: 
        peGrid = dict(zip(pnames,gp))
        try:
            pgrid.remove(peGrid)
        except:
            pass
        
    if verbose:
        print("grid points remaining: ",len(pgrid))
        
    return pgrid,gridRuns

# customised learning rate scheduler
# considering slope of validation loss
class lossGradientLR(tf.keras.callbacks.Callback):
    """gradually descend learning rate if the loss defined my the model is not descending at desired rate"""
    def __init__(self,initial_learning_rate=1e-3,patience=5,
                 slope=0.25,factor=0.75,lr_least=1e-10,verbose=False):
        super(lossGradientLR, self).__init__()
        self.initial_learning_rate = initial_learning_rate
        self.patience = patience
        self.slope = -slope
        self.factor = factor
        self.lr_least = lr_least
        self.verbose = verbose
        self.loss = []
        self.lr = [initial_learning_rate]
        self.lastAdjust = 0
        
    def Gradient_schedule(self,epoch):
        """scheduled learning rate manipulation"""
        flag1 = False
        flag1 = (epoch-self.lastAdjust)>self.patience # min epoch before adjust
        
        flag2 = False
        try:
            flag2 = (self.loss[-1]-self.loss[-2])>0 and (self.loss[-2]-self.loss[-3])>0
            # if two continuous epochs have increasing validation loss
        except:
            pass
        
        # slope of validation loss
        lossGrad = (self.loss[-1]-self.loss[self.lastAdjust])
        lossGrad/= len(self.loss[self.lastAdjust:])
        
        # if slope of validation loss not descending at slope or flag2
        if (flag1 and lossGrad>self.slope) or (flag2):
            self.lr.append(max(self.lr[-1]*self.factor,self.lr_least)) #min lr_least
            self.lastAdjust = epoch # update last adjust epoch
        
        if self.verbose:
            print("\n\nslopeOfLoss:%.2f"%lossGrad," @ epoch:%d"%epoch, "---- learning_rate:",self.lr[-1],"\n")
        
    def on_epoch_end(self,epoch,logs={}):
        """on end of each epoch"""
        # fetch validation loss
        self.loss.append(logs.get('val_loss'))
        #invoke learning rate calculator
        self.Gradient_schedule(epoch)
        
    def on_epoch_begin(self,epoch,logs={}):
        """beginning of each epoch"""
        # update model learning rate
        tf.keras.backend.set_value(self.model.optimizer.lr, self.lr[-1])
        
# report learning rate to tensorboard
# due to custom lr_scheduler
class LRTensorBoard(tf.keras.callbacks.TensorBoard):
    """report to tensorfboard about the updates created by lossGradientLR"""
    def __init__(self, log_dir, **kwargs):
        super().__init__(log_dir=log_dir, **kwargs)

    def on_epoch_end(self, epoch, logs=None):
        logs = logs or {}
        logs.update({'learning_rate': backend.eval(self.model.optimizer.learning_rate)})
        super().on_epoch_end(epoch, logs)

def nnTrain(modelFunc, mNamePrefix, hparam, sLogFile, logBaseDir, loss, metrics,
            fitparams, htune=False, savePeak=False, eStop=False, verbose=0):
    """set up the environment and train the network
    modelFunc : function that creates a network architecture according to the passed parameters
    mNamePrefix : string identifier for naming
    hparam : dict of hyperparameter
    sLogFile : hyperparameter and results consolidation log file name with path
    logBaseDir : base directory of tensorboard logs
    loss : built-in loss or user defined loss function
    metrics : list of metrics to monitor
    fitparams : dict of kwargs to pass on to fit method except callbacks
    htune : boolean, enable/disable hypertuning callback
    savePeak : boolean, enable/disable saveBest callback
    eStop : boolean, enable/disable earlyStop callback
    verbose : 0,1,2 verbosity
    """
    # Random consistency seed
    np.random.seed(129)
    tf.random.set_seed(129)
        
    # create model
    model = modelFunc(hparam)
        
    # name it
    global gridRuns
    mname = mNamePrefix + "_%03d_"%(len(gridRuns)+1) + datetime.datetime.now().strftime("%d%b_%I%M%P")
        
    # create tensorboard logs & callbacks
    logdir = os.path.join(logBaseDir, mname)
    tensorboard_cb = tf.keras.callbacks.TensorBoard(logdir, histogram_freq=1, embeddings_freq=1)
        
    # initiate learning rate reporter
    lReport = LRTensorBoard(logdir)
        
    # learnin rate decay scheduler
    lr = hparam.get('learningRate')
    lr_schedule = lossGradientLR(lr,factor=0.1,verbose=bool(verbose))
    
    # callback to report hyperparameters to tensorboard
    hypertune = hp.KerasCallback(logdir,hparam)
    
    # metrics-->monitor
    if type(metrics[0])==str:
        nMonitor = metrics[0]
        monitor = "val_" + metrics[0]
    else:
        nMonitor = metrics[0].__name__
        monitor = "val_" + metrics[0].__name__
    
    # callback to save best model weights
    saveFile = logBaseDir + '/' + mname + '_weights.{epoch:02d}-{' + nMonitor + ':.2f}.h5'
    saveBest = tf.keras.callbacks.ModelCheckpoint(filepath=saveFile,monitor=monitor,
                                              mode='max',save_best_only=True)
    
    # early stop callback
    earlyStop = tf.keras.callbacks.EarlyStopping(monitor=monitor,mode='max',
                                                 min_delta=0.01,patience=15,restore_best_weights=True)
    
    # collect callbacks
    cbs = [tensorboard_cb,lr_schedule,lReport]
    cbs.append(hypertune) if htune else None
    cbs.append(saveBest) if savePeak else None
    cbs.append(earlyStop) if eStop else None
        
    # optimisers
    optim = optimizers.RMSprop(learning_rate=lr,rho=0.9,momentum=0.1, epsilon=1e-07)
    
    # compile model
    model.compile(optimizer=optim,loss=loss,metrics=metrics)
    
    # update fitparams
    fitparams.update(dict(callbacks=cbs,verbose=verbose))
    
    # model fitting
    with tf.device('/device:GPU:0'):
        logger = model.fit(**fitparams)
        
    # obtain peak results
    (p_metric,p_epoch) = (np.max(logger.history.get(monitor)),
                     np.argmax(logger.history.get(monitor)))
    
    # summarise hparams with results
    with tf.summary.create_file_writer(logBaseDir +'/hparam_tuning').as_default():
        hp.hparams(hparam)
        
    # log the results
    storage = []
    storage.extend(list(hparam.values()))
    storage.extend([p_metric,p_epoch])
    storage.extend([mname])
    
    file = open(sLogFile,'ab')
    pickle.dump(storage,file)
    file.close()
    
    pgrid,gridRuns = gridConsolidate(hparam,sLogFile,False)
    
    return model,logger, mname
#Clear any logs from previous runs try: !rm -rf ./logs/ os.mkdir('logs') except: os.mkdir('logs') file = open("logs/MobileUNet_tuning.har",'wb') # reset log file file.close() #above file creation & log reset to be commented after setting up a tuning framework

def hTune(modelFunc, mNamePrefix, pgrid, sLogFile, logBaseDir, nSearch, loss, metrics, fitparams):
    """Neural Networks HyperTuning function
    modelFunc : function that creates a network architecture according to the passed parameters
    mNamePrefix : string identifier for naming
    pgrid : list of gridpoints each as a dict of hyperparameter
    sLogFile : hyperparameter and results consolidation log file name with path
    logBaseDir : base directory of tensorboard logs
    nSearch : int, number of randome grid points to run gridsearch
    loss : built-in loss or user defined loss function
    metrics : list of metrics to monitor
    fitparams : dict of kwargs to pass on to fit method except callbacks
    """
    
    startTime = datetime.datetime.now()
    lapTime = startTime
    
    global gridRuns
    pgrid,gridRuns = gridConsolidate(pgrid,sLogFile, False)
    
    # metrics-->monitor
    if type(metrics[0])==str:
        nMonitor = metrics[0]
        monitor = "val_" + metrics[0]
    else:
        nMonitor = metrics[0].__name__
        monitor = "val_" + metrics[0].__name__
    
    for gp in np.random.choice(np.array(pgrid),nSearch,replace=False):
        
        # update fitparams for hypertuning with reduced dataset
        #fitparams.update(dict(steps_per_epoch = 8, validation_steps = 2))
        
        _, logger, _ = nnTrain(modelFunc, mNamePrefix, gp, sLogFile, logBaseDir, loss, metrics,
                fitparams, htune=True, savePeak=False, eStop=True, verbose=0)
        
        print("grid :%03d"%(len(gridRuns)+1))
        print("gridPoint:", gp)        
        print(nMonitor + ':%.2f'%logger.history.get(nMonitor)[0] + ' '*8 +
              monitor + ':%.2f'%logger.history.get(monitor)[0])
    
        t2 = datetime.datetime.now() - lapTime
        th = int(t2.seconds/60/60)
        tm = int(np.mod(t2.seconds,3600)/60)
        ts = np.mod(t2.seconds,60)
        tstr1 = "elapsed lap time %02d:%02d:%02d"%(th,tm,ts)

        t2 = datetime.datetime.now() - startTime
        th = int(t2.seconds/60/60)
        tm = int(np.mod(t2.seconds,3600)/60)
        ts = np.mod(t2.seconds,60)
        tstr2 = "   elapsed total time %02d:%02d:%02d"%(th,tm,ts)

        print(tstr1, tstr2, '\n')

        lapTime = datetime.datetime.now()

Part A¶

DOMAIN: Entertainment
• CONTEXT: Company X owns a movie application and repository which caters to movie streaming to millions of users who are logged on subscription basis. Company wants to automate the process of cast and crew information in each scene from a movie such that when a user pauses on the movie and clicks on cast information button, the app will show details of the actor in the scene. Company has an in-house computer vision and multimedia experts team who need to detect faces from screen shots from the movie scene. The data labelling is already done, since there higher time complexity is involved
• DATA DESCRIPTION: The dataset comprises of images and its mask for corresponding human face.
• PROJECT OBJECTIVE:To build a face detection system.

Steps and tasks:

  1. Import and Understand the data
    A. Import and read ‘images.npy’.
    B. Split the data into Features(X) & labels(Y). Unify shape of all the images.
    Imp Note: Replace all the pixels within masked area with 1.
    Hint: X will comprise of array of image whereas Y will comprise of coordinates of the mask(human face).
    Observe: data[0], data[0][0], data[0][1].
    C. Split the data into train and test[400:9].
    D. Select random image from the train data and display original image and masked image.

# lets create function to display dimensions to study from the image dataset
def imsize(images):

    dh=[]
    dw=[]
    dc=[]
    ds=[]

    for i in images:
        try:
            (h,w,c)=i.shape
        except:
            (h,w)=i.shape
            c=1
        dh.append(h)
        dw.append(w)
        dc.append(c)
        ds.append(len(i.shape))
    
    minh = min(dh)
    minw = min(dw)
    minc = min(dc)
    mins = min(ds)

    maxh = max(dh)
    maxw = max(dw)
    maxc = max(dc)
    maxs = max(ds)
    
    # display the dimension limits
    print((minh,minw,minc,maxs,maxh,maxw,maxc,maxs))
    
    return dh,dw,dc,ds

# split the images and labels
# also standardise the number of channels in each image
img = []
lab = []
msk = []
n4s = []
for n,[i,l] in enumerate(images):
    # check channels
    try:
        h,w,c = i.shape
    except: # single channel images
        h,w = i.shape
        nimg = np.zeros((h,w,3),dtype='uint8') # create 3 channels
        nimg[:,:,0] = i
        nimg[:,:,1] = i
        nimg[:,:,2] = i
        i = nimg
        h,w,c = i.shape
    if c!=3: # if number of channels more than 3
        n4s.append(n)

    # append images & labels
    img.append(i)
    lab.append(l)
    
    # create masked images
    mask = np.zeros((h,w),dtype='uint8')
    for box in l:
        a,b = np.multiply(list(box.get('points')[0].values()),[w,h]).astype(int)
        c,d = np.multiply(list(box.get('points')[1].values()),[w,h]).astype(int)
        cv2.rectangle(mask,(a,b),(c,d), 1, -1)
        
    # append masked images
    msk.append(mask)

def dice(y,pred):
    return 2 * tf.reduce_sum(pred*y)/(tf.reduce_sum(pred+y)+1) #+1 as epsilon

In [25]:
def loss(y,pred):
    # cross entropy loss for classification
    l1 = tf.keras.losses.binary_crossentropy(y,pred)
    # log loss(negative) from dice coeficient
    l2 = -tf.keras.backend.log(dice(y,pred)+1e-37) #1e-37 as epsilon
    return l1+l2

# lets define a method to create the Unet architecture
def MobileUNET(params={}):
    """method to create MobileNet base Unet analogous neural topology"""
    # read parameters
    alpha,train_from,upConvFilter = list(params.values())[:3]
    
    # Random consistency seed
    np.random.seed(129)
    tf.random.set_seed(129)
    
    # define MobileNet as the skeleton for this Unet alias attempt
    model = MobileNet(input_shape=(128,128,3),include_top=False,alpha=alpha,weights='imagenet')
    
    # fetch skip connections for feature mapping
    skip1 = model.get_layer('conv_pw_1_relu').output
    skip2 = model.get_layer('conv_pw_3_relu').output
    skip3 = model.get_layer('conv_pw_5_relu').output
    skip4 = model.get_layer('conv_pw_11_relu').output
    
    # name & identitfy the bottle neck output
    bottleNeck = model.get_layer('conv_pw_13_relu').output
    
    # transposed convolutions and concatenations to upsample from bottleneck
    build4 = Convolution2DTranspose(upConvFilter,kernel_size=(3,3),strides=(2,2),
                                    padding='same',name='build_conv_4')(bottleNeck)
    cat4 = Concatenate(name='build_cat_4')([build4,skip4])
    build3 = Convolution2DTranspose(upConvFilter,kernel_size=(3,3),strides=(2,2),
                                    padding='same',name='build_conv_3')(cat4)
    cat3 = Concatenate(name='build_cat_3')([build3,skip3])
    build2 = Convolution2DTranspose(upConvFilter,kernel_size=(3,3),strides=(2,2),
                                    padding='same',name='build_conv_2')(cat3)
    cat2 = Concatenate(name='build_cat_2')([build2,skip2])
    build1 = Convolution2DTranspose(upConvFilter,kernel_size=(3,3),strides=(2,2),
                                    padding='same',name='build_conv_1')(cat2)
    cat1 = Concatenate(name='build_cat_1')([build1,skip1])
    
    build0 = Convolution2DTranspose(upConvFilter,kernel_size=(3,3),strides=(2,2),
                                    padding='same',name='build_conv_0')(cat1)
    
    # introduce a convolutional layer with sigmoid function to obtain the desired mask with 0~1
    conv_mask = Conv2D(1,kernel_size=1,activation='sigmoid',name='mask_generator')(build0) #(transConv)
    
    # reshape to desired shape
    mask_layer = Reshape((128,128),name='output')(conv_mask)
    
    model = Model(inputs = model.input, outputs = mask_layer)
    
    for l in model.layers[:train_from]:
        l.trainable=False
    
    return model

# read image names and extract the contents of the zip file
with zipfile.ZipFile('training_images.zip', 'r') as zfile:
    fnames = zfile.filelist
    zfile.extractall('.')
fnames = [f.filename for f in fnames]

# using haarcascade
face_cascade = cv2.CascadeClassifier('haarcascade_frontalface_default.xml')

# detect face bounding boxes
metaArray = []
for i,file in enumerate(fnames): # loop to iterate through all images in folder
    face_image = np.array(Image.open(file)) # read image
    gray = cv2.cvtColor(face_image, cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY) # convert 3 channel rgb image to grayscale image
    faces = face_cascade.detectMultiScale(gray) # detect the bounding boxes for faces in the grayscale image
    face_count=len(faces)
    for n,(x, y, w, h) in enumerate(faces):
        metadata = [x,y,w,h,n+1,face_count,file.split('/')[-1]]
        metaArray.append(metadata)

# store the metadata in a pandas dataframe
metaDf = pd.DataFrame(metaArray,columns=['x','y','w','h','nth face','total faces','image name'])

# display few data
display(metaDf.head())

# save the metadata as a csv file
metaDf.to_csv('metadata.csv',index=False)

def meta(fpath):
    """returns dictionary of metadata"""

    return dict(name=name,path=fpath)

# define vgg face model topology
def vgg_face():
    model = Sequential()
    model.add(ZeroPadding2D((1,1),input_shape=(224,224, 3)))
    model.add(Convolution2D(64, (3, 3), activation='relu'))
    model.add(ZeroPadding2D((1,1)))
    model.add(Convolution2D(64, (3, 3), activation='relu'))
    model.add(MaxPooling2D((2,2), strides=(2,2)))
    
    model.add(ZeroPadding2D((1,1)))
    model.add(Convolution2D(128, (3, 3), activation='relu'))
    model.add(ZeroPadding2D((1,1)))
    model.add(Convolution2D(128, (3, 3), activation='relu'))
    model.add(MaxPooling2D((2,2), strides=(2,2)))
    
    model.add(ZeroPadding2D((1,1)))
    model.add(Convolution2D(256, (3, 3), activation='relu'))
    model.add(ZeroPadding2D((1,1)))
    model.add(Convolution2D(256, (3, 3), activation='relu'))
    model.add(ZeroPadding2D((1,1)))
    model.add(Convolution2D(256, (3, 3), activation='relu'))
    model.add(MaxPooling2D((2,2), strides=(2,2)))
    
    model.add(ZeroPadding2D((1,1)))
    model.add(Convolution2D(512, (3, 3), activation='relu'))
    model.add(ZeroPadding2D((1,1)))
    model.add(Convolution2D(512, (3, 3), activation='relu'))
    model.add(ZeroPadding2D((1,1)))
    model.add(Convolution2D(512, (3, 3), activation='relu'))
    model.add(MaxPooling2D((2,2), strides=(2,2)))
    
    model.add(ZeroPadding2D((1,1)))
    model.add(Convolution2D(512, (3, 3), activation='relu'))
    model.add(ZeroPadding2D((1,1)))
    model.add(Convolution2D(512, (3, 3), activation='relu'))
    model.add(ZeroPadding2D((1,1)))
    model.add(Convolution2D(512, (3, 3), activation='relu'))
    model.add(MaxPooling2D((2,2), strides=(2,2)))
    
    model.add(Convolution2D(4096, (7, 7), activation='relu'))
    model.add(Dropout(0.5))
    model.add(Convolution2D(4096, (1, 1), activation='relu'))
    model.add(Dropout(0.5))
    model.add(Convolution2D(2622, (1, 1)))
    model.add(Flatten())
    model.add(Activation('softmax'))
    return model
